 HELL CREEK PROJECT DINO DIG
 OLDEST T-REX UNEARTHED 
 A record eight specimens of Tyrannosaurus rex have been discovered and unearthed over the last five years at the Hell Creek Project Dinosaur Dig in northeastern Montana. Excavation of the oldest T-rex on record, estimated to be about 68 million years old, was completed during the 2003 field season.
